                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think the solution to the risk vs reward issue etc is a simple one.
<br />

<br />
A Charmed Mob cannot be buffed up.
<br />

<br />
Make the Charm spell overwrite all other spells to prevent pre-buffing.
<br />

<br />
Make the Charm spell non-stackable with any other spell while in effect. So no Offensive Spells cast on the pet will stick, spells landed from attackers will stick.
<br />

<br />
Therefore the problem SOE sees with overpowered charm pets in the past are solved, no more 100% DPS + Group buffs to make the charmed pet an insane killing machine are solved.
<br />

<br />
The present issue with a charmed pet nerfed to 25% normal damage returning to 100% when charm breaks causing insta-death is solved.
<br />

<br />
No alternate tables, no re-tweaking of all expansion mobs.
<br />

<br />
Change the Charm, Leave the Mobs alone.
<br />

<br />
Have Charm Wipe out all beneficial buffs on sucessfully landing on a Mob.
<br />
Make Charm non-stackable to all beneficial spells while in effect.
<br />

<br />
Aurbo Skyfyre
<br />
Kane Bayle</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
