                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm terribly on the fence here, somewhere between NO change is acceptable and a minor reduction in DPS in return for inherant MR reductions.  I like Ompy's idea somewhat.  The net reward would be lessened risk in terms of charms breaking early and the cost for it would be *some what* diminished DPS (but still enough to get a mob down to near 0 when the mob is slowed at perhaps 80% of it's life.   It would still allow some utility for charm as DPS and a means to solo.  In the event that charm where changed, I would expect to see all the proper debufs (-mr) to be associated with it as well as the charm exp penalty removed.
