</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I don't like the direction they are going with enchanter charms. What they should do is remove the weakening of npc's when charmed. Just make various npcs more likely to break charm much like slow is mitigated. The enchanter should get a message at the beginning that lets them know if they have a naturally 'unruley' mob.
