                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was honestly very happy without charm when crowd control was a useful and neccesary function in groups. Once PoP came out and CC was nerfed charm became our only interesting skill but sadly once they nerfed it the enchanter class became largely redundant especially on raids. When I started an enchanter I picked the class because we were needed - once that changed I didn't feel any attraction to the game at all. It's ulitmately the decision to marginalize enchanters that led me to quit the game. If I'd wanted to be an class just for the sake of enjoyment I would have picked something else, but I went with an enchanter because we were important and valueable. Until that's restored I doubt EQ will have much to offer me.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />When a government has ceased to protect the lives, liberty and property of the people, from whom its legitimate powers are derived, and for the advancement of whose happiness it was instituted, and so far from being a guarantee for the enjoyment of those inestimable and inalienable rights, becomes an instrument in the hands of evil rulers for their oppression. - Declaration of Independence of the State of Texas.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
