                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I posted this just now on the SOE forum. May as well do it here too:
<br />

<br />
IMHO, The charm issue is overblown.
<br />
Charm has alway been a sideshow for most chanters, never a central role. Its like defining resurrection as the central role of Necromancers. Yeah sure, necros are needed and wanted as rezzers in raids/exp groups. Many a raid has been saved by Necromancers rezzing. But YOU WILL NEVER get a necromancer to say that his/her role in the game is to ressurect people! Necromancers do so much other fun stuff. Its like that with chanters. We do charm, we are great at it. Chanters do much other fun stuff too APART from charm. Other stuff thats a lot more vital and relevant to our class and the to the people we play/raid with. Why so much emphasis on charm for enchanters now?
<br />

<br />
Charm is sideshow, a distraction.
<br />
Work on our defensive abilities, our whacko aggro, our damaged RvR CC abilities at high end - where Tank OT is prefferable and safer compared to deaded chanters who die on the first mez resist. Txevu or RS trash killing chanters on every other pull? Is that considered balanced CC? Fix that first!
<br />

<br />
PS:
<br />
If SOE wants to have charm used in every exp group we join, then the inherent risk of charm break MUST ALSO BE CAPPED. Yes, cap the risk of a break if you want to cap the DPS of the pet. Its as simple as that.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Quellious Cold Fury</span>
<br />
Greif 70 Coercer Chanter
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=217293" target="_blank" class="postlink">Stuffs of Nonsense</a>
<br />
Baene 57 Disciple Monkey
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=217816" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tools of Evil!</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
